      "content": "i mean \"cynically\" is a pretty strong word to use for people who had different ideas about strategy. what about the more militant groups or the idea that actual systemic change only happened because of the threat of unrest? was that just a side note or was it actually a legitimate part of the movement's effectiveness?",
